<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-08-21T08:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-08-21T08:36:00-05:00" n="872" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d872">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/844: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at San José</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Chase</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                            José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-21T08:00:00-05:36"><hi rend="italic">August
                                            21, 1919, 8 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received August 24.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Resignation of Federico Tinoco was presented to his Congress
                                yesterday afternoon by Quiros who was named by it for the balance of
                                the term. Extra session then declared ended. I am arranging for
                                meeting to comply with the instructions by cable August 19th, 3
                                p.m.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Chase</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>